24/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Swiss Economy Minister Joseph Deiss, who is also governor of the EBRD, told Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica on Monday (23 May) that political stability, resolving Kosovo's final status, and co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal are vital to attracting foreign investment in Serbia.
Deiss described Serbia's economic future as bright, but urged continued reforms.
(Swiss Info - 23/05/05)
